	     Cairo - Gunmen attacked a packed mosque in Egypt's restive North Sinai province on Friday and set off a bomb, killing 54 and  injuring at least 75 people, health and police officials said. Health ministry spokesperson Khaled Megahed said at least 75 people were wounded in the attack and no deaths had been reported yet. The attack took place near the provincial capital of El-Arish during weekly prayers, police officials said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  